# Files excluded from the archive uploaded to EAS Build.
#
# package-lock.json is deliberately withheld. EAS runs `npm ci` whenever it
# finds a lockfile, and `npm ci` can never succeed in this project:
# @aws-amplify/data-construct ships *bundled* copies of @opentelemetry/core and
# zod, which npm does not record in the lockfile, so `npm ci` always fails with
#
#   npm error code EUSAGE
#   npm error Missing: @opentelemetry/core@2.0.0 from lock file
#
# This reproduces locally even after `rm -rf node_modules package-lock.json &&
# npm install`. Without the lockfile in the upload, EAS falls back to
# `npm install`, which works. The lockfile stays in git for local development.
package-lock.json

# Nothing below is needed to build the app.
dist/
dist-native/
.amplify/
node_modules/
